cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

The paper introduces a novel deep learning framework for map inference from GPS trajectories, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks and trajectory descriptors. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of iterative trajectory mean shift and classification of junctions, which are related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves the processing of natural language descriptions of maps, which is related to Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
